Bootstrap: localimage
From: ./ubuntu_22.04.sif

%post
    # Update package list and install required software
    apt-get update && \
    apt-get install -y --no-install-recommends \
        python3 \
        python3-pip \
        jq \
        ca-certificates && \
    rm -rf /var/lib/apt/lists/*

    # Install pytest for the validation suite
    pip3 install --no-cache-dir pytest

    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Prepare initial data expected by the assignment/test framework
    # ------------------------------------------------------------------
    # Create the directory structure
    mkdir -p /home/user/data

    # Create the CSV file with exact required contents
    cat > /home/user/data/metrics.csv <<'EOF'
server,cpu,memory
web-01,65,70
app-02,88,91
db-01,92,80
cache-01,55,40
web-02,83,95
EOF

    # Ensure the top-level /home/user directory is writable by
    # the unprivileged user that will run the container.
    chmod 0777 /home/user

%labels
    chmod 755 /home/user

    Author="Auto-generated definition for monitoring alert task"

%help
    This container provides the initial state for a monitoring-alert
    assignment.  It already contains:
      • /home/user/data/metrics.csv with predefined rows.
      • Python 3 and pytest for running the verification suite.
      • jq (and standard coreutils) in case the student prefers CLI tools.
    Students are expected to generate /home/user/alerts/high_usage.json
    and /home/user/alerts/process.log according to the task description.